01:34:42,491 --> 01:34:44,292
<font color="#A9F5F2">[Indistinct chatter]</font>

2099
01:34:44,393 --> 01:34:45,659
All right. Come on,
let's play some cards.

2100
01:34:45,760 --> 01:34:48,429
<font color="#A9F5F2">[Cheers, lively chatter]</font>

2101
01:34:51,333 --> 01:34:53,067
- Wow!
- All right.

2102
01:34:53,168 --> 01:34:56,404
- This is awesome, man.
- Good to see you, brother.

2103
01:34:56,505 --> 01:34:58,671
- Good to see you.
- Pull up a chair.

2104
01:34:58,772 --> 01:35:01,708
Oh, look.
I got my old spot back.

2105
01:35:01,809 --> 01:35:03,076
You got all cleaned up.

2106
01:35:03,177 --> 01:35:05,379
I was prepping these dudes
for the homeless wizard look.

2107
01:35:05,480 --> 01:35:06,713
Yeah. I got a little
shave and a haircut.

2108
01:35:06,814 --> 01:35:08,715
I didn't want to scare
anybody, you know.

2109
01:35:08,816 --> 01:35:12,152
Hey, what do we call you?
Rolly? Nathan? What...?

2110
01:35:12,253 --> 01:35:13,686
Rolly.

2111
01:35:13,787 --> 01:35:15,488
- Rolly it is.
- Yeah. Rolly.

2112
01:35:15,589 --> 01:35:17,590
- Welcome home.
- Thank you very much.

2113
01:35:17,691 --> 01:35:19,258
So, rolly, am I the first
woman you've seen

2114
01:35:19,359 --> 01:35:20,493
since you've been out?

2115
01:35:20,594 --> 01:35:22,028
Dottie, you're the first.

2116
01:35:22,129 --> 01:35:23,396
You and me, come on,
let's go. Let's do it.

2117
01:35:23,497 --> 01:35:25,565
You're the first, dottie.

2118
01:35:25,666 --> 01:35:28,334
- <font color="#A9F5F2">[Laughing]</font>
<font color="#F5DA81">- Rolly: </font> What's the game?

2119
01:35:28,435 --> 01:35:30,736
Five-card draw. I think
that's your favorite, isn't it?

2120
01:35:30,837 --> 01:35:33,739
Same shit-game that he always
plays, nothing's changed.

2121
01:35:33,840 --> 01:35:34,940
<font color="#A9F5F2">[Laughing]</font>

2122
01:35:35,041 --> 01:35:36,474
Ante up, you guys.

2123
01:35:36,576 --> 01:35:39,545
Well, whether you
know it or not, rolly,

2124
01:35:39,646 --> 01:35:42,548
you have become a bit
of a hero in these parts.

2125
01:35:42,649 --> 01:35:44,049
A lot of people
were happy to see

2126
01:35:44,150 --> 01:35:47,418
that monstrosity of a house
hit the dust.

2127
01:35:47,519 --> 01:35:48,753
- Local hero.
- You're the guy.

2128
01:35:48,854 --> 01:35:50,588
Ballsy move.

2129
01:35:50,689 --> 01:35:53,457
Your three years in prison was
worth getting rid of that house.

2130
01:35:53,559 --> 01:35:56,060
- Absolutely.
- Hey, what happened to money bags?

2131
01:35:56,161 --> 01:35:57,728
They got him on some treatment.
He's in remission.

2132
01:35:57,829 --> 01:35:59,430
- They went back to California.
- No kidding?

2133
01:35:59,531 --> 01:36:01,098
Are they ever coming back
to the island?

2134
01:36:01,199 --> 01:36:02,399
I don't think they should,

2135
01:36:02,500 --> 01:36:04,834
knowing that rolly's
back in town.

2136
01:36:04,936 --> 01:36:06,235
Oh, yeah.
What am I thinking?

2137
01:36:06,336 --> 01:36:07,938
<font color="#A9F5F2">[Lively chatter]</font>

2138
01:36:08,039 --> 01:36:09,372
All right, ante in.

2139
01:36:09,473 --> 01:36:11,775
My only regret, rolly,
is that you missed

2140
01:36:11,876 --> 01:36:13,743
the Chicago concert that night.

2141
01:36:13,844 --> 01:36:16,312
My God! Best show
I've ever seen.

2142
01:36:16,413 --> 01:36:17,881
The entire island was there.

2143
01:36:17,982 --> 01:36:19,582
- They were great.
- Yeah. All three encores.

2144
01:36:19,683 --> 01:36:21,650
Everybody had a great time,
especially the band.

2145
01:36:21,751 --> 01:36:23,085
<font color="#F5DA81">Rolly: </font>
Why is that?

2146
01:36:23,186 --> 01:36:24,820
Jennifer blew them
in the parking lot.

2147
01:36:24,921 --> 01:36:27,389
- I forgot about that.
- Jennifer? The whole band?

2148
01:36:27,490 --> 01:36:30,325
- Lee loughnane, for sure.
- Definitely Jimmy pankow.

2149
01:36:30,426 --> 01:36:33,062
No. No. Not pankow. It was
loughnane and Robert lamm.

2150
01:36:33,162 --> 01:36:34,563
<font color="#F5DA81">Dottie: </font> No.
